just eight weeks from now east germans will 
make more money pay fewer taxes and see some of their savings 
triple in size 
but prices will surely rise parts of bank accounts may be 
frozen and workers will still make only about a third as much as 
their neighbors in the west 
that is the scenario both germanys predict will begin to unfold 
july 2 when the countries proclaim economic unity and begin one of 
historys most extraordinary experiments 
east germans will suddenly have greater access to better goods 
but the mere act of buying them may begin to put hundreds of 
thousands of their countrymen out of work as east germans shun 
their countrys goods for better western ones 
factories and former staterun enterprises will be free to 
compete in a free market shorn of communist regulation but they 
will face western competition and many will surely fold 
while all of this is happening investors may begin moving in to 
tap the new consumer market and the cheap labor in the new economic 
frontier the investment may create new jobs raise living 
standards and ultimately bring parity between east and west 
i am optimistic that there will be an economic awakening after 
a period of pain said juergen wagner an economist with 
commerzbank in frankfurt 
chancellor helmut kohl and prime minister lothar de maiziere of 
east germany meeting tuesday in bonn confirmed the two nations 
will officially share an economy july 2 
this is true unification to most germans for whom the cost of a 
heating bill the size of their pension and the price of their 
apartment is more important than the ideological debate on the role 
of a united germany in a changing world 
anybody who thinks west germany will simply load up tons of west 
german marks and ship them across the border while east germany 
burns its virtually worthless old currency is right 
officials say enough uncirculated cash is sitting in the west 
german bundesbank to supply east germanys banks east germany this 
week began destroying tons of its own reserves to create space in 
its treasury 
in the fall a new currency is expected to go into circulation 
for both countries 
many details still need to be worked out but by july 2 there 
likely will be one german economy 
west germanys agreement to swap most of the east german marks 
for west german marks at a 11 rate cleared a basic hurdle to 
unifying the countries 
west germanys central bank had said anything but a 21 trade 
could weaken the mighty west german mark trigger inflation and 
lead to higher interest rates 
but on monday it bowed to political pressures agreeing to back 
the 11 plan put forward by the kohl government 
economists like prospective parents trying to predict the 
appearance of their children can only speculate on how the 
offspring of this odd economic marriage will look 
they do agree that three things will happen in east germany 
after july 2 east german prices will rise thousands will be out 
of work and some inflation may occur in west germany 
nearly 9 million east germans make on average 960 marks per 
month nearly 90 percent of the women work so most families are 
twoincome households 
right now that 960 marks is worth about 320 west german marks 
190 at the official 31 exchange rate but in july east germans 
will get their full wages in west german marks about 560 
the catch is that west germans now average nearly triple that 
salary and consumer goods are priced accordingly by the free 
market 
east germans now pay relatively little for housing food is 
heavily subsidized and jobs guaranteed 
so what could happen in july economists predict prices will 
rise to more closely reflect the market in the new nation 
well see higher prices for groceries energy public tariffs 
railroads and other things that are highly subsidized said 
rudolf zwiener of the german institute for economic research in 
west berlin 
zwiener said east germany will need some sort of price 
protection to keep goods and rents affordable in the short term 
one advantage east germans will have he said is that they will 
pay a smaller share of taxes under west germanys progressive tax 
system 
but he said 1 million to perhaps 2 million could be jobless in a 
year east german factories and businesses will close as more east 
germans spend their new west german marks on better west german 
products 
huge unemployment also is likely in the vast public sector 
east german factories also have about 153 billion in debts 
incurred by the old socialist regime west germany proposes 
converting that to west marks at a 21 rate and assigning the debts 
to the enterprises 
the west germans also want a 11 conversion rate on personal 
savings of up to about 2300 with amounts above that converted at 
a 21 rate 
east germany is pressing for a higher ceiling zwiener predicts 
the ceiling likely will be doubled but with limits on how much 
east germans can withdraw right away 
many economists predict at least some inflation and higher 
interest rates when so many more west german marks flood the 
market zwiener predicts it will be slight 
wagner said he believes there will be enough growth to offset 
the effects of inflation and higher interest rates 
the capital that must go into east germany will come from 
all over the world he said the japanese will invest a lot in 
the country 
its already happening even though there is no real legal 
system in place yet to allow it japans yamaha motorcycles took 
over a storefront in downtown east berlin west germanys dresdner 
bank has moved into a room at the citys palace hotel 
five weeks ago budget rentacar also checked into a 
fourthfloor room at the palace set up two desks and began renting 
western cars 
were here unofficially said a woman who answered the door 
everybody is 
</TEXT>
