the fear of fire has gripped this city 
after a series of blazes that left at least 11 people dead and 
25000 homeless 
on wednesday 4000 makeshift homes in three shantytowns on the 
northwestern outskirts of the capital were destroyed in a fire 
officials said 
hundreds of poor men women and children wailing and pleading 
for food stopped traffic and stoned cars saying relief efforts 
were inadequate 
on tuesday fire engulfed 5000 straw and mud huts in the 
northeastern district on monday 3000 shacks were consumed by 
flames in the center of the city and 11 people were killed 
last week fires destroyed 600 shops and new delhis only 
convention center 
fires are common in northern india during the hot dry summer 
when a spark from an unextinguised match can spawn an inferno 
within minutes the latest outbreak is worse than usual but 
investigators say they have found no evidence of foul play 
