<TEXT>
the heirs of edward steichen a pillar 
of new yorks museum of modern art are battling the museum over an 
800000 painting by matisse that was bequeathed to the 
photographers 6yearold greatgranddaughter 
although steichen and his family have been longtime benefactors 
the museum is refusing to hand over the painting which has been in 
the photography pioneers family since henri matisse gave it to him 
in 1908 
the museum argues the painting loaned to them by steichens 
youngest daughter in 1973 was meant as a permanent gift even 
though kate steichen in her will left the work to her grandniece 
ariana rodina calderone stahmer of pennington nj 
