however the bill does mandate hearings on revoking the charter 
and deposit insurance of a bank or sampl within 30 days after the 
institution and two or more of its senior officers are convicted of 
moneylaundering 
in the hearings regulators would have to consider the extent of 
involvement in moneylaundering by senior managers of the bank or 
sampl the institutions cooperation with law enforcement officials 
and steps it had taken to prevent the practice 
in addition the bill would prohibit anyone convicted of 
moneylaundering from working in a financial institution again and 
would raise from 500 to 5000 the possible fines for civil 
violations 
similar legislation in the senate is awaiting action by the 
senate banking committee 
