ltryptophan has been linked to 21 deaths and more than 1500 
reports of illness from a disorder called eosinophiliamyalgia or 
ems 
the fda last month declared ltryptophan a major public health 
problem and expanded its recall of the supplement commonly sold 
in health food stores as a remedy for insomnia appetite control 
and depression 
