was declared a state emergency thus eliminating any need for 
approval from the cities 
in florida the spraying that began this morning was to cover a 
16squaremile area near miami international airport in about a 
month millions of sterile medflies will be released to foul up the 
pests breeding cyle 
the target area will be covered with pesticide in a 
concentration of 24 ounces or about three tablespoons of 
malathion per acre that compares with 31 ounces of malathion per 
acre routinely sprayed throughout florida to control mosquitoes 
the female medfly found tuesday in a port everglades back yard 
trap brought to 10 the number of medflies discovered in south 
florida in as many days 
