<TEXT>
sweden and norway which were in the 
path of the radioactive cloud from the chernobyl explosion four 
years ago said thursday many of their lakes and rivers are still 
dangerously contaminated 
finland wedged between its scandinavian neighbors and the 
soviet union escaped with less contamination because it had no 
rainfall for several weeks after the accident april 26 1986 
winds carried radiation from the nuclear reactor in the soviet 
ukraine to the wilderness of central sweden and norway 1200 miles 
to the northwest 
radioactive cesium soaked into the ground contaminating lichen 
and other plants eaten by wildlife 
finnish scientists said they were continuing studies to 
determine if fallout had increased the incidence of cancer first 
results should be available next year 
swedish researchers said 14000 lakes or about 15 percent 
still contained fish too contaminated to eat it may be 30 years 
before the lakes will be considered safe 
fish have been found containing radiation levels 66 times higher 
than the permitted level according to researchers who examined 644 
lakes 
in norway newspapers reported that the level of cancercausing 
substances in the most effected regions was 10 times normal levels 
in plants and up 20 times above normal in topsoil 
experts said parts of norway will live with effects of fallout 
well into the next century 
