more liberalized emigration policy is written into law by the 
soviet parliament 
at the summit with gorbachev in malta bush expressed the hope 
that normalizing trade relations would give a boost to the soviet 
economy 
the trade agreement is needed to grant the soviet union the 
trade status of most favored nation qualifying it for the 
lowest tariffs granted to any other country 
currently soviet exports into the united states bear duties as 
much as 10 times higher than imports from other nations 
us officials have predicted that trade between the two 
countries could double or even triple over the next three years 
with a new trade agreement 
