will save 168 billion in 1991 through 1994 the departments 
current fiveyear spending plan and another 18 billion during 
1995 through 1997 
he said the stealth cutback would lower the projected cost of 
the plane from 754 billion to 611 billion a saving of 143 
billion over the life of the program 
cheney also said he intends to cut planned purchases of the c17 
longrange transport plane and the navys a12 attack aircraft and 
