cutbacks under a start treaty with the united states 
the cutbacks now being negotiated in geneva would trim the 
size of the soviet arsenal rowny told the reserve officers 
association 
in the meantime he said soviet strategic forces longrange 
nuclear missiles bombers and submarines are being upgraded to 
provide for a powerful arsenal after the treaty takes effect 
the ussr is intent on retaining its claim to the status of 
a superpower equal to the united states that only firstrate 
nuclear forces can provide rowny said 
the soviets are upgrading their strategic nuclear weapons far 
more aggressively than is the united states he said for instance 
rowny said the soviets are making their landbased ss18 
intercontinental ballistic missiles more accurate and more powerful 
while continuing to deploy ss24s with 10 warheads both in silos 
and as mobile weapons 
