are more likely to be below the poverty level the pervasiveness of 
drugs and the school dropout rate about one in four 18 and 
19year olds have dropped out of school it said and among 
hispanics the figure was 45 percent 
the report said that at a time when the conditions of children 
call for more flexibility in the schools many school systems are 
becoming more rigid in their operation and less accommodating to 
students needs 
