<TEXT>
pesticidelaced insect bait rained upon 
neighborhoods west of miami on thursday as authorities sought to 
snuff out a mediterreanean fruit fly infestation that could 
threaten floridas 14 billion citrus industry 
it was the first assault on medflies in dade county in three 
years state biologists meanwhile examined fly traps about 25 
miles north to check the scope of the infestation 
hopefully what weve done is the beginning of the end for the 
medflies said maeve mcconnell a spokeswoman for the eradication 
task force in miami were keep our fingers crossed 
a helicopter loaded with syrupy insect bait spiked with 
malathion blanketed a 16squaremile area near miami international 
airport where the first flies were found last week 
ms mcconnell said experts from the florida department of 
agriculture will be checking traps around fort lauderdale this week 
for any indication of more medflies whose larvae eat the core of 
fruit a female medfly found tuesday near port everglades was found 
not to be pregnant she said 
officials have speculated the fly could have been trapped inside 
a ship or plane 
as of late thursday 10 medflies had been discovered in south 
florida scientists have determined that for every medfly found in 
a trap there are probably 500 to 1000 fles nearby according to 
the state agriculture department 
present plans call for three more aerial applications in the 
miami area in may with a mixture of about 24 ounces of malathion 
per acre that compares with 31 ounces of malathion or about 
four tablespoons per acre sprayed throughout florida to control 
mosquitoes 
the use of malathion to kill medflies has caused controversy in 
southern california but there were no organized protests reported 
in miami on thursday 
a few school officials and parents complained that afternoon 
spraying coincided with release of students from class and one 
environmentalist blasted the effort 
there is no choice involved here the malathion is sprayed 
directly on places where people live i have a problem with that 
said joseph podgor jr dade county chairman of the friends of the 
everglades at least if its sprayed on fruits you can wash it 
off 
officials advised remaining indoors and keeping small pets under 
cover during spraying malathion which can irritate eyes also can 
damage paint on automobiles wateruse restrictions were waived for 
the spray zone to allow residents to rinse their cars 
next month millions of sterile medflies will be released in a 
slightly larger area in an attempt to break the insects onemonth 
breeding cyle 
a quarantine went into effect wednesday for about a 
100squaremile area west of downtown miami that requires 
inspection of all medflyhost produce including some 250 
varieties of fruits and vegetables leaving the area 
the last medfly spraying in florida occurred in 1987 in hialeah 
a city neighboring miami 
