<TEXT>
in 1944 jews imprisoned in a nazi concentration 
camp in czechoslovakia performed verdis requiem the catholic 
mass for the dead and in a few days were themselves deported to 
death camps 
to commemorate those who participated in the requiem at the 
terezin camp near prague the verdi work was being performed 
thursday night at carnegie hall by the 150member new york choral 
society with robert decormier conducting 
the 1944 performance was organized as the germans were losing 
ground in world war ii and trying to cover up atrocities in the 
concentration camps the terezin camps nazi commandant wanted a 
program to show the red cross that terezin was a model ghetto 
the young conductor rafael schachter held at terezin organized 
jews in the camp to perform the work their lines in latin 
included therefore when the judge shall be seated nothing 
shall be held hidden any longer no wrong shall remain unpunished 
despite the camp commandants promise to schachter he and 
nearly all the 150 singers and musicians were deported to death 
camps a few days after the performance 
the carnegie hall performance was being introduced by rabbi 
