<TEXT>
researchers in four states have now linked a 
single manufacturer of the dietary supplement ltryptophan to a 
potentially deadly blood disorder which has struck 1500 people 
federal epidemiologists from south carolina and new york 
reported thursday that many of their states cases of 
eosinophiliamyalgia syndrome a painful blood disorder linked late 
last year to ltryptophan occurred after patients took the product 
from just one japanese manufacturer 
researchers from oregon and minnesota reported similar findings 
wednesday at a national epidemiology conference at the centers for 
disease control 
the ltryptophan use thats causing people to get ill is 
virtually universally from one particular company said dr ed 
kilbourne a cdc specialist in eosinophiliamyalgia syndrome or 
ems significantly fewer users were unaffected if they were using 
that companys products 
ltryptophan has been widely taken in this country by dieters 
insomniacs and people fighting depression before its recall by the 
food and drug administration earlier this year it was widely sold 
in health food stores 
several japanese manufacturers make ltryptophan and their 
products are sold under a host of different brand names the cdc 
has refused to specify the company whose product has been 
implicated because there are still a number of ongoing 
investigations which are not yet complete kilbourne said 
but the washington post on thursday quoted a spokesman for the 
showa denko co one of japans largest chemical manufacturers as 
saying the studies showed a strong statistical association 
between our product and ems 
showa denko has already been named in at least one lawsuit from 
an ems patient a 20 million claim from a oregon woman 
but it is important to note that the studies do not 
independently identify the precise cause of ems said the showa 
denko spokesman bob schwadron 
the fact that one specific manufacturer has been implicated 
means the likely cause of the illness is some sort of product 
contamination and not simply ltryptophan itself kilbourne said 
but researchers still dont know what sort of contaminant might be 
responsible in that manufacturers product or how it got there 
this is still a very complicated investigation kilbourne 
said 
