deputies voting against one abstaining and one absent 
the government enjoys the confidence of parliament 
announced athanassios tsaldaris president of the chamber 
mitsotakis new democracy party won 150 seats in april 8 
elections after failing to win a majority in elections last june 
which removed the socialists from office another inconclusive poll 
was held in november 
coalition governments ruled from june to april 
mitsotakis formed a government after the democratic renewal 
party pledged to support it in parliament he has said he intends 
to govern for a full 4year term 
mitsotakis has promised to renew negotiations with the united 
states on an expired defense agreement and to recognize the state 
of israel 
he has blamed socialist policies for the economic troubles and 
stressed that sacrifices will be required for a recovery 
the government has the honor to present a policy that is 
painful and unpleasant he said it saddens us but we have to 
carry it out because there is no other choice and it can lead the 
country to revival 
mitsotakis announced increases in public utility rates cuts in 
government spending and widespread privatization 
papandreou predicted mitsotakis steps would cause the 
immediate shriveling of peoples wages 
the measures also drew fire from some of greeces powerful trade 
unions 
the general confederation of greek workers raised the 
possibility of protest strikes 
