confirmed the ship was fishing inside the exclusive zone woolf 
said the ship was observed with its fishing gear in the water he 
said 
the last time the coast guard seized a soviet fishing vessel in 
the north pacific was in may 1989 when the trawler novoelnya was 
captured with 940 metric tons of pollock aboard that case was 
recently settled when the soviets agreed to pay 275000 in fines 
burgess said 
both seizures were in an area of the bering sea known as the 
doughnut hole 
the doughnut hole is a circular area surrounded by soviet 
and us exclusive fishing zones where coast guard and american 
fisheries officials suspect foreign ships await the cover of night 
or bad weather to sneak into the fishrich us zone 
the united states and several other nations with highseas 
fishing fleets have clashed for years over the rich north pacific 
fisheries 
