floodwaters gushed through texas on thursday after 
more than 24 hours of thunderstorms forcing the evacuation of two 
towns and campers to the roofs of their cars authorities mobilized 
the national guard and high wind damaged an air force base 
at least three people drowned in texas and two were missing from 
the storms which were photographed by space shuttle discoverys 
astronauts orbiting 380 miles above earth one family was rescued 
from a tree 
flooding in nearby southcentral oklahoma also forced 
evacuations and closed highways 
the national weather service reported up to 16 inches of rain 
overnight in some areas of texas as storms carrying at least nine 
tornadoes hopscotched across the state 
i have never seen it rain this hard its raining so hard that 
you can hardly see out said laura goehl of stephenville 
southwest of fort worth where more than 150 people waited out the 
storm in shelters overnight and into thursday morning 
the texas national guard sent 35 people and 20 trucks to help 
evacuate 200 people from brownwood southeast of abilene and from 
a small rural community on the brazos river near weatherford just 
west of fort worth 
i can tell you that in horseshoe bend everyone has been moved 
out there is no one left said juanette kaddatz a spokeswoman 
for parker county emergency spokeswoman officials had no estimates 
of its population 
ms kaddatz said 70 percent of the parker county community was 
under water by midafternoon thursday and the water was rising 
police in brownwood reported all major traffic routes flooded 
some several feet deep two of the three deaths were reported in 
that town 
the big flood in 1957 was somewhat worse than this but the 
water is still rising said brownwood police lt bg watson 
about 20 miles northeast of brownwood at least 130 people were 
evacuated early thursday in the area of proctor as proctor lake 
rose and the rain continued 
many had to be rescued by boat after their cars and campers were 
