<TEXT>
early in the nbc drama fall from grace tv 
preacher jim bakker anguished and seeking comfort from an old 
minister friend confesses a moment of adultery with jessica hahn 
he then says this 
trying to build ptl into a worldwide ministry the government 
attacking me about taxes the newspapers writing stories about me 
my marriage falling apart a live television show six days a week 
the pressures never let up 
i i just wasnt thinking straight 
later in the show he snaps at an aide why does everyone want 
to nail jim bakker to the cross 
it may be that those to whom the tv preacher refers had no 
advance knowledge his sad story would become a bad tv movie this 
has come to pass so they can stop singing if i had a hammer 
nbc bought the tv rights from the bakkers for an undisclosed sum 
and got their help in making what has emerged as fall from 
grace it stars kevin spacey and bernadette peters who play the 
bakkers and lose 
airing sunday the movie dramatizes their descent from fiscal 
and evangelical heaven after the devil in the form of the justice 
department halts bakkers works and his multimilliondollar ptl 
empire 
itll probably get skyhigh ratings even though its opposite 
abcs the story of the beach boys a dramatization of the 
private woes of the lads who became a major cultural force just by 
singing surfin usa 
but nbcs twohour bakkerarama sure gives awful a bad name 
directed by karen arthur with a 10ton touch its written by ken 
trevey as if he sought divine guidance and got a busy signal 
although it tries to show the pain and frailty of the bakkers 
