<TEXT>
alderman michael mcgee scares some people 
disgusts others he certainly has them talking 
mcgee began recruiting street gang members and others in march 
for a black panther community militia and threatened to send it 
on terrorist attacks if his demands for improvements in the inner 
city werent met by 1995 likely targets would be sporting events 
and busy freeways he said 
he claims the militia already has 500 members 
one anticrime activist predicts people are going to get hurt 
the mayor says mcgee should resign unless he renounces violence 
but also urges calm and asks people to look beyond mcgees rhetoric 
to examine the poverty and violence in the inner city 
mcgee says he has worked within the system most of his public 
career whether as a vietnam war medic political activist or 
alderman but he says hes fed up with the systems failure to 
improve the life of poor minorities in one of the nations most 
segregated cities 
ive been doing things the socalled right way mcgee said 
im opposed to violence but i think at some point it becomes 
cowardliness on the part of the black community to keep letting 
people abuse us 
mcgee wants the city to spend 100 million on training and jobs 
for innercity residents redraw aldermanic districts to improve 
minority representation on the common council and implement some of 
a task forces recommendations for improving unemployment crime 
teen pregnancy and other social ills among minorities 
he is one of three blacks on the 16member council 
in his five years as an alderman representing a mostly black 
poor crimeridden district on milwaukees north side mcgee has 
staged other protests to call attention to the inner city 
he once led a whistleblowing demonstration during a visit by 
jimmy carter claiming the former presidents effort to build homes 
in innercity areas was a facade that helped few if any 
another time he wore a paper bag over his head for the annual 
common council photograph saying he was embarrassed to be seen 
with the council after it approved a city budget that cut services 
to the inner city 
many people including some constituents were angered by 
mcgees threats some called for his removal from office 
this black panther thing has caught me completely off guard i 
think its going to get a lot of people hurt said queen hyler 
who heads the anticrime group stop the violence that recently was 
praised by president bush 
she asked mcgee to resign and has threatened to circulate 
petitions in his district seeking a recall election 
ms hyler first met mcgee in 1981 when they worked together in a 
movement that helped win a 600000 settlement for the family of a 
22yearold black man who died in police custody 
mcgee used to demonstrate and march like everyone else she 
said but in recent years hes been a little bolder once he got 
some political clout behind him 
