demands may be met in the meantime donegan said he senses mcgee 
may be toning down some threats 
i think what mike is saying to people who want to be in his 
militia now is a lot more positive i think he has without 
admitting it backed down from some of his earlier more violent 
statements donegan said 
mcgee who worked for the original black panthers group in the 
1970s counts among his heroes such black leaders as nat turner 
who led a slave revolt marcus garvey a jamaican activist in the 
1920s and malcolm x the assassinated black muslim leader 
he said his militia will be used for neighborhood patrols and 
economic boycotts while also undergoing military training were 
going to continue to do a lot of nonviolent things between now and 
1995 he said 
id worry more if i wasnt doing what im doing it would take 
a bigger toll he said i would suffer twice as much if youre 
not doing anything itll eat you alive 
mcgee said he would remain on the common council even though the 
mayor and others have said he should resign if he continues to 
advocate violence 
i have no plans of giving up my participation i think thats 
what a politician should be about leading the people he said 
in 1995 when i start kicking butt in milwaukee ill still be an 
alderman 
