ceremony the man took her away on the honeymoon in a garbage can 
it was very influenced by the 1960s theater of the absurd it 
played once in a beatnik coffee house and that was it 
waters continued making films with his baltimore buddies until 
the breakthrough with mondo trasho 
it was the story of a hitrun driver on one hideous day in her 
life he recounted it starred divine and in the end divine 
died in a pig pen and the virgin mary appeared to her 
in multiple maniacs divine was raped by a 15foot broiled 
lobster pink flamingos was about a battle between the filthiest 
people alive female trouble was about a criminal who wanted to 
be famous so badly that she got the electric chair that was like 
the oscar in her chosen profession desperate living was about 
the worst town you could live in when youre so embarrassed about 
your life you have to move there 
polyester was a comedy about the hell of suburban life where 
everything smells bad it was released in odorama hairspray 
was a musical comedy about a teen dance show cry baby is a 
juvenile delinquent comedy 
so you can see that my sense of humor has been the same from 
the very beginning 
despite the outrageousness of his themes waters claims the 
critics have been good to me since the very beginning you get bad 
press when you start believing the nice things that you all sign 
bad reviews rex reed gave us the best where do these people 
come from where do they go when the sun goes down isnt there a 
