<TEXT>
twenty years ago skip ewing saw glen 
campbell perform on television something clicked 
at the time ewing was about to start school today hes 26 and 
one of the youngest country music performers signed to a recording 
contract with a major label 
i was about 4 when i got my first guitar ewing recalled in 
an interview i cant remember a time when i didnt play 
i know i sang the theme to rawhide and i watched the glen 
campbell goodtime hour i wanted to play just like glen 
in the 1990s ewing is one of country musics fresh faces just 
as campbell was in the late 60s 
the handsome wellspoken singersongwriter is laying the 
foundation for a solid career doing something he genuinely enjoys 
his single its you again reached the top 10 of the 
country music popularity charts in february burnin a hole in my 
heart and the gospel according to luke were top 10 hits last 
year 
ewing has released two albums coast of colorado and the 
will to love the latter has many cuts with little more than a 
fingerpicked acoustic guitar 
he was born in redlands calif but lived throughout the 
country because his father spent 11 years moving from city to city 
in the navy ewing worked at the opryland usa theme park in 
nashville for 2 seasons as a singerdancer in a live production 
tracing the history of country music 
he also made a living as a songwriter and has written album cuts 
recorded by kenny rogers willie nelson george strait george 
jones conway twitty ricky van shelton and others 
since launching his solo career he has been the opening act at 
country concerts with such headline performers as the judds randy 
travis alabama and reba mcentire 
ewing who also plays the fivestring banjo and mandolin 
understands that hes fortunate to have a recording contract at a 
relatively youthful age but he quickly adds that he worked 
diligently for it 
i was in town three years before it happened he said it 
was a short time compared with some people but i had been doing it 
for a heck of a long time i had been singing and writing songs and 
traveling 
im not a very patient person sometimes i want things to 
happen thats one of the things i need to work on accept things 
as they are 
i set awful big goals i work hard at what i do he said 
i figured there are a lot of singers in town a lot of 
songwriters and a lot of guitar players and if i can do all of 
them well i have a chance 
his balladoriented music focuses on romance in the album the 
will to love the song its you again is about the pain of 
love the cut karen is about the disintegration of a 
relationship shes makin plans is about devotion please 
dont leave me now deals with family love 
it seems like my voice is suited to ballads ewing said i 
like to sing emotional things i feel like im sharing something 
when i do that i enjoy singing things that allow me to feel like 
im saying something that im expressing something its like 
being an actor sometimes 
he has written all the songs he has recorded 
songwriting is very much a craft and an art i dont just 
settle for things sometimes it takes hours to find one line a 
place where different emotions mix 
i feel like i have a lot to offer when i go and do a show 
its not a job its something i love to do the music i perform 
and write is all a part of me by sharing that with an audience i 
feel im sharing things important to me i feel that what i share 
with people is worthwhile and im not wasting somebodys time with 
my music 
the song the will to love used an instrument rarely used in 
country music a cello ewing who didnt want to use traditional 
country instruments such as fiddles and steel guitars said it 
allowed him to be more intimate 
on his next lp he plans to use another instrument rarely heard 
in country music a saxophone 
i dont mind taking chances ewing said 
campbell his old idol surprised him recently after hearing 
that ewing was a longtime fan of his he came by the studio 
during my first album just to say hi that was a big deal to me 
and still is 
</TEXT>
