<TEXT>
worried about heavy volatility on the tokyo 
stock exchange japanese market officials have been pressing to 
limit us sales of securities pegged to tokyos bellwether nikkei 
stock index 
they have made their concerns aware to us said bob 
shabazian a spokesman for the american stock exchange where eight 
nikkei put and call warrants trade 
the warrants which some have been blamed for adding to the 
tokyo exchanges volatility are used as a hedge against movements 
in the 225share nikkei index 
the warrants give their holders the right to purchase or sell 
the cash equivalent of the nikkei index at a certain price on a 
certain date put warrants give the right to sell and call warrants 
the right to buy 
speculators also use the warrants to bet on the direction of the 
market for example buying put warrants if they believe the nikkei 
will decline as a result the value of put warrants rises as the 
nikkei falls 
since january the nikkei has plunged nearly 30 percent in 
value raising the demand among investors in the united states and 
elsewhere for the warrants 
in january the kingdom of denmark became the first issuer to 
list nikkei put warrants on the amex since then a number of us 
investment houses have followed suit including goldman sachs amp 
co painewebber group inc and salomon inc 
but american investment houses have agreed to voluntarily halt 
issuing further warrants at the request of japanese officials 
a spokesperson for salomon said the firm is not going to issue 
any additional warrants without the approval of japanese 
authorities 
shabazian said discussions between amex and japanese stock 
exchange officials over the warrants have been ongoing even before 
denmark launched the first 
we have an informationsharing agreement with the 
japanese shabazian said but he added weve had no formal 
request from them to limit trading in the options 
in what some market watchers believe could be the last issue for 
some time the financing and export credit institute of the 
norwegian commercial banks ltd issued 75 million warrants and 
raised about 28 million on thursday the transaction was managed 
by goldman sachs 
a spokesman goldman sachs noted that having just completed a 
deal were not currently considering another but he added the 
