<TEXT>
firstquarter earnings for the nations big three 
automakers will be more than twothirds below last years profits 
analysts said thursday 
the companies are expected to report next week that the drop in 
earnings was caused mainly by drastic production cuts in the united 
states and economic troubles in brazil 
a spot check of analysts thursday showed forecasts that general 
motors corps quarterly earnings would be down about 70 percent 
from the 155 billion the company earned during the first three 
months of 1989 which was the best quarter gm had since the second 
quarter of 1984 
ford motor cos earnings should be down about 75 percent from 
the 164 billion the company earned during the period last year 
according to the analysts chrysler corp may show a marginal 
increase from the 351 million in profits it posted during the 
first quarter of 1989 the analysts said 
the earnings are going to be almost a yawn said john kirnan 
of kidder peabody amp co in new york people have been bracing 
for the weakened earnings report the bigger question is when are 
we going to get the turn 
auto company executives and industry analysts have predicted 
that the first half of the year would be tough and that things 
would pick up in the second half 
theyll make more money in the second quarter than they did in 
the first quarter said analyst david healy of barclaysbzw in 
new york in the second quarter earnings will still be below 
last year but the comparisons wont be as bad as the first 
quarter 
a rebound in the second half may be delayed kirnan said 
the car and truck sales numbers have certainly gotten back 
into a sluggish territory and with interest rates continuing to 
escalate it may choke off a major turn in secondquarter and 
