projected cost from 754 billion to 611 billion but would raise 
the cost of individual planes to more than 800 million according 
to cheney 
northrop also is competing for a role in a new generation 
aircraft known as the advanced tactical fighter which will replace 
the air forces f15 
cheney still wants 750 planes built but would push back 
purchases two years from 1994 to 1996 
the northrop spokesman said the impact of that change is minimal 
because the aircraft is not in fullscale development 
